# Test node-style self-references: a workspace package importing its own
# package name through its own package.json 'exports' field.
# https://nodejs.org/api/packages.html#self-referencing-a-package-using-its-name
#
#  * a self-reference to an exports subpath generated by another Bazel
#    package resolves to that target (lib/pkg/index.ts -> //lib/pkg/sub)
#  * a self-reference to an exports entry within the same target resolves
#    to nothing (lib/pkg/self.ts importing '@lib/pkg')
#  * self-references take precedence over the same package name being
#    importable from an ancestor project (the root depends on @lib/pkg,
#    which must not shadow lib/pkg's self-references with
#    //:node_modules/@lib/pkg, a circular dependency)
#  * a self-reference matching a '*' exports subpath pattern resolves to
#    the expanded target (lib/pkg/index.ts importing '@lib/pkg/feat/x'
#    -> //lib/pkg/feat). Note the npm_package does not collect '*'
#    pattern entries, a known limitation.
workspace(name = "pnpm_workspace_exports")
